Description: TMJOs metapackage — pulls in the entire TMJOs experience
 Installing this package on a base Debian 13 (trixie) system gives
 you the complete TMJOs setup:
   * Branding (wallpapers, logos, Plymouth)
   * System identity (/etc/os-release etc.)
   * TMJMenu (popup search) + TMJDock (proprietary dock)
   * dconf system-wide overrides (dark mode, fonts)
   * TMJPad text editor
 .
 The Recommends list mirrors what the ISO ships preinstalled —
 VSCode, Docker, Git, Calamares installer, GNOME Tweaks, Evolution
 (Exchange mail), zram-tools / preload (RAM efficiency), dev fonts,
 network tools, etc.
 .
 On TMJOs systems, `sudo apt upgrade tmjos` will pull the latest
 versions of every component package, providing the post-release
 update mechanism for the Debian-based v2.0 line.
